title: Gordon Brown
deleted: '''James Gordon Brown''' {{post-nominals|country=GBR|HFRSE}} (born 20 February 1951) is a British politician who was [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom]] and [[Leader of the Labour Party (UK)|Leader of the Labour Party]] from [[2007 Labour Party leadership election (UK)|2007]] to [[2010 United Kingdom government formation|2010]]. He served as [[Chancellor of the Exchequer]] from [[1997 United Kingdom general election|1997]] to [[2007 Labour Party (UK) leadership election|2007]]. Brown was [[Member of Parliament (United Kingdom)|Member of Parliament]] (MP) from [[1983 United Kingdom general election|1983]] to [[2015 United Kingdom general election|2015]], first for [[Dunfermline East (UK Parliament constituency)|Dunfermline East]] and later for [[Kirkcaldy and Cowdenbeath (UK Parliament constituency)|Kirkcaldy and Cowdenbeath]].
